This paper is about neural machine translation (NMT), which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the computer science category. The paper proposes a novel approach for NMT that explicitly models translated and untranslated content through parts-to-wholes assignment. This approach involves a variant of routing-by-agreement mechanism, which is a popular technique in deep learning and falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI). The paper also involves extensive experiments and analysis, which are common in machine learning and fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves interpreting the results of the experiments, which is a common task in computer vision (cs.CV) and NLP (cs.CL). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, and cs.CV, in that order.
